President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring June 16-22, 2013, as National Small Business Week. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of small businesses in America's economy and acknowledges the contributions they make to job creation and innovation. The President highlights various initiatives his administration has undertaken to support small businesses, including tax cuts, increased access to capital, and assistance with exporting products. He also mentions efforts to protect innovators through patent system reforms, promote global competitiveness through trade agreements, and provide affordable healthcare options for small business employees. The proclamation encourages Americans to recognize the role of small businesses and participate in relevant programs and activities.